Cell population annotation

1. Introduction

This document takes the QCd, normalized, scaled, clustered, marker identified data and annotates cell populations.

4. Annotation with sc-type

## SC-TYPE
## Get reference data
source("/data/Shih_Lab/scRNAseqNilisha/Tools/sctype/gene_sets_prepare.R")
source("/data/Shih_Lab/scRNAseqNilisha/Tools/sctype/sctype_score_.R")
db_ = "/data/Shih_Lab/scRNAseqNilisha/Tools/sctype/ScTypeDB_short.xlsx";
# Set tissue as immune system
tissue = "Immune system"
# Prepare marker gene list
gs_list = gene_sets_prepare(db_, tissue)

# get cell-type by cell matrix
es.max = sctype_score(scRNAseqData = WT_TG_Filt_Scaled[["RNA"]]@scale.data, scaled = TRUE, gs = gs_list$gs_positive, gs2 = gs_list$gs_negative)

# merge by cluster
cL_resutls = do.call("rbind", lapply(unique(WT_TG_Filt_Scaled@meta.data$seurat_clusters), function(cl){
    es.max.cl = sort(rowSums(es.max[ ,rownames(WT_TG_Filt_Scaled@meta.data[WT_TG_Filt_Scaled@meta.data$seurat_clusters==cl, ])]), decreasing = !0)
    head(data.frame(cluster = cl, type = names(es.max.cl), scores = es.max.cl), 10)
}))

# List top cell types
cL_resutls %>% group_by(cluster) %>% top_n(n = 1)   
## # A tibble: 26 × 3
## # Groups:   cluster [26]
##    cluster type                  scores
##    <fct>   <chr>                  <dbl>
##  1 20      Macrophages            206. 
##  2 19      CD8+ NKT-like cells     70.5
##  3 7       Neutrophils             39.8
##  4 4       Mast cells             101. 
##  5 0       Naive CD8+ T cells      56.2
##  6 10      Naive CD8+ T cells      36.0
##  7 6       Natural killer  cells  312. 
##  8 11      Effector CD8+ T cells   47.0
##  9 9       Immature B cells       505. 
## 10 22      Natural killer  cells  172. 
## # … with 16 more rows
# Add sctype metadata
WT_TG_Filt_Scaled@meta.data$sctype = ""
for(j in unique(cL_resutls$cluster)){
  cl_type = cL_resutls[cL_resutls$cluster==j,]; cl_type = cl_type[order(cl_type$scores, decreasing = T), ]
  if(cl_type$scores[1]>0){
    WT_TG_Filt_Scaled@meta.data$sctype[WT_TG_Filt_Scaled@meta.data$seurat_clusters == j] = as.character(cl_type$type[1])
  } else {
    WT_TG_Filt_Scaled@meta.data$sctype[WT_TG_Filt_Scaled@meta.data$seurat_clusters == j] = "Unknown"
  }
}

# Run permutation test
prop_test <- sc_utils(WT_TG_Filt_Scaled)
prop_test <- permutation_test(
    prop_test, cluster_identity = "annotatedRNA_snn_res.0.75",
    sample_1 = "WT", sample_2 = "TG",
    sample_identity = "orig.ident",
    n_permutations = 10000
)

permutation_plot(prop_test)

png("proportion.png")
permutation_plot(prop_test)
